i## Introduction	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iA while back, I became interested in esoteric programming	/	tilde.team	70
ilanguages. More specifically, I became interested in the	/	tilde.team	70
imechanisms involved in interpreting and compiling their	/	tilde.team	70
icode. It’s a little-known field in the world of computer	/	tilde.team	70
iscience, yet I find this culture to be very rich and	/	tilde.team	70
ichallenging. That’s why I wanted to talk about it here, in	/	tilde.team	70
ithe form of a blog post. This is mainly my personal	/	tilde.team	70
iperspective and feedback; the views expressed are my own.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i## Definition	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iAn esoteric programming language is a programming language	/	tilde.team	70
idesigned around one or more strange or unusual ideas.	/	tilde.team	70
iGenerally, these languages are created as a joke or to meet	/	tilde.team	70
ia challenge, and are not intended to solve any specific	/	tilde.team	70
iproblem.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
